753
00:44:26.312 --> 00:44:30.112
IL6 and IL6 receptor. Vikas Gupta decided to make this a

754
00:44:30.252 --> 00:44:33.652
little more translational, so he did this with Venetoclax and Venetoclax-sensitive

755
00:44:33.712 --> 00:44:37.592
cells and showed the same thing. And then Shannon showed that, in fact, it was the

756
00:44:37.632 --> 00:44:39.952
most important thing in the stroma, because if she knocked out

757
00:44:40.952 --> 00:44:44.602
IL6 from the stromal cells, they no longer protected from the Venetoclax killing.

758
00:44:47.032 --> 00:44:50.452
How does this happen? Well, we thought it would change protein expression, and we

759
00:44:50.492 --> 00:44:52.272
do see a change in

760
00:44:53.312 --> 00:44:57.092
one cell line. Again, the same one I was just talking about, that Mcl1 goes up

