00:45:31.912 --> 00:45:35.222
hours. And you can see we don't see a lot of protein changes in these three cell

772
00:45:35.272 --> 00:45:38.252
lines. However, you see a lot of phosphorylation changes.

773
00:45:39.052 --> 00:45:42.812
And when we look at what those are, curious enough in these cells, I'm just

774
00:45:42.852 --> 00:45:46.812
showing two of the lines here. Bcl2l11, so BIM

775
00:45:46.852 --> 00:45:50.212
comes up again as a protein that's phosphorylated during this

776
00:45:50.252 --> 00:45:51.612
process.

777
00:45:52.492 --> 00:45:56.201
And through data I don't have time to show, but it's all published at this

778
00:45:56.212 --> 00:45:59.892
point. What we were able to show is it's also phosphorylated on two sites,

779
00:45:59.932 --> 00:46:03.732
serine 77 and serine 69, and that's a

780
00:46:03.792 --> 00:46:05.432
MEK-dependent fashion, so

781
00:46:07.072 --> 00:46:10.112
downstream of JAK. We do obviously see some Mcl1.

782
00:46:10.172 --> 00:46:13.592
We see it all going up at the message level, but not so much at the protein level.

783
00:46:13.632 --> 00:46:17.572
And that when we treat with IL6, we actually see a shift

784
00:46:17.612 --> 00:46:21.252
of BIM binding from Bcl2 to Mcl1, explaining

785
00:46:21.272 --> 00:46:24.412
resistance to things like ABT-737 and Venetoclax.

786
00:46:24.872 --> 00:46:28.632
So based on this, Vikas Gupta and Jonathan Koffman actually now have a trial going

787
00:46:28.652 --> 00:46:32.412
where they're treating patients, pre-treating with Tocilizumab to block IL6

788
00:46:32.472 --> 00:46:34.532
receptor prior to Venetoclax treatment in

789
00:46:34.592 --> 00:46:37.652
refractory multiple myeloma.

790
00:46:40.632 --> 00:46:42.812
But we're still interested in BIM phosphorylation.

791
00:46:43.112 --> 00:46:47.032
And Jason Konichpoo was a student in the lab, and he was looking at this, and

