800
00:47:16.272 --> 00:47:19.872
Therefore, these are all due to phosphorylation.

801
00:47:20.112 --> 00:47:23.992
And they were in cells where we didn't have RAF mutations and things like that

802
00:47:24.032 --> 00:47:24.912
as well.

803
00:47:26.052 --> 00:47:28.332
And he actually found this also in patient samples too.

804
00:47:28.412 --> 00:47:31.372
So there's a lot of constitutive phosphorylation going on.

805
00:47:31.702 --> 00:47:35.032
And so we went back into the proteomics data, and what Becca found was that there

