00:49:09.928 --> 00:49:13.468
opportunity, potentially, for co-targeting here.

834
00:49:15.808 --> 00:49:19.648
And then what I want to finish off with in the last few minutes

835
00:49:19.728 --> 00:49:22.888
is another case of an

836
00:49:23.348 --> 00:49:27.068
intrinsic change, and that was this 11;14

837
00:49:27.128 --> 00:49:30.388
translocation. This is found in about 15% to 20% of myeloma patients.

838
00:49:30.788 --> 00:49:34.368
It results in juxtaposition of cyclin D1 to the IgH

839
00:49:34.408 --> 00:49:36.828
enhancer, so high expression of cyclin D1.

840
00:49:37.388 --> 00:49:41.308
And pre-clinical data from Martine Amiel suggested that these patients may be

841
00:49:41.848 --> 00:49:44.708
more sensitive to venetoclax. However, the

842
00:49:44.948 --> 00:49:48.868
original venetoclax trial didn't actually take heed

843
00:49:48.908 --> 00:49:50.488
to that and just treated all patients.

844
00:49:50.818 --> 00:49:53.568
And what you can see is they had a 21% overall response rate.

845
00:49:54.238 --> 00:49:54.528
But

846
00:49:55.608 --> 00:49:58.948
some people just decided to only put 11;14 patients on it because

847
00:49:59.588 --> 00:50:01.128
40% of those patients responded,

848
00:50:02.068 --> 00:50:04.268
while only 6% of the patients who didn't have it.

849
00:50:04.308 --> 00:50:05.948
And so there was something intrinsic about this.

850
00:50:06.328 --> 00:50:08.428
We were actually looking at this in patient samples.

851
00:50:08.468 --> 00:50:12.348
This is about 70 overall. And we were able to mimic this just by doing

