00:50:50.268 --> 00:50:53.428
ratios, but these differences were not, for the most part, big enough to actually

865
00:50:53.438 --> 00:50:56.808
see a difference where you could predict a patient was going to be sensitive or

866
00:50:56.828 --> 00:51:00.468
resistant. It's just statistically, as a group, there was this difference.

867
00:51:01.048 --> 00:51:02.948
And so he wanted to look further, and so he

868
00:51:04.088 --> 00:51:07.188
looked at all differentially expressed genes between sensitive and resistant

869
00:51:07.928 --> 00:51:10.588
in cell lines as well as in patient samples.

870
00:51:11.088 --> 00:51:14.928
And there was a lot of overlap here because he took a meta

871
00:51:14.968 --> 00:51:17.328
gene set of these upregulated genes.

872
00:51:17.378 --> 00:51:19.768
They were highly enriched in the patient samples.

873
00:51:19.798 --> 00:51:23.708
And this just shows a map of all of them, and anything that was black

874
00:51:23.748 --> 00:51:27.708
was significant in at least one of either the patient samples or the

