00:51:27.728 --> 00:51:31.448
cell lines. The ones in red are the only ones that were actually

876
00:51:31.508 --> 00:51:35.048
overlapping significance in both.

877
00:51:35.568 --> 00:51:39.468
And none of those actually say BCL2 or anything like that on

878
00:51:39.508 --> 00:51:42.858
it. We didn't see any changes there, and that's because the mRNA level, we actually

879
00:51:42.868 --> 00:51:46.468
don't see any differences in BCL2, MCL1, or

880
00:51:47.468 --> 00:51:50.208
BCL-X expression in these patient samples.

881
00:51:50.608 --> 00:51:54.448
So what is different? And what was different was that while these are plasma cells,

882
00:51:54.788 --> 00:51:58.308
they actually expressed genes that were more consistent with B cells.

883
00:51:58.568 --> 00:51:59.188
So

884
00:52:00.248 --> 00:52:02.648
CD20, CD79A,

885
00:52:03.648 --> 00:52:06.968
PAX5, and suggesting that they have a slightly altered

886
00:52:06.978 --> 00:52:07.858
differentiation,

887
00:52:08.748 --> 00:52:12.408
and that maybe it's the differentiation state that's actually helping set this.

888
00:52:14.888 --> 00:52:18.658
We also, at this time, when I showed you this earlier about all these

889
00:52:18.688 --> 00:52:22.348
samples we tested, 16 of these patients were actually treated with venetoclax,

890
00:52:22.808 --> 00:52:25.388
and this ex vivo test actually predicted which ones would

891
00:52:26.228 --> 00:52:27.348
respond or not.

892
00:52:28.188 --> 00:52:32.048
If the IC50 was below 100 nanomolar, those patients pretty

893
00:52:32.068 --> 00:52:34.608
much all responded. If it didn't,

894
00:52:35.737 --> 00:52:37.048
they didn't respond.

895
00:52:37.868 --> 00:52:41.828
Vikas actually extended this to a larger group cohort, found that it still held

896
00:52:41.848 --> 00:52:42.048
that the

897
00:52:43.928 --> 00:52:46.948
overall response rate in sensitive patients was close to 90%, where it was only

898
00:52:46.988 --> 00:52:50.128
about half here. Part of the reason we started seeing some of these respond was

899
00:52:50.147 --> 00:52:53.688
because of dexamethasone was added to more of these patients.

900
00:52:54.068 --> 00:52:57.148
And that resulted in an overall

901
00:52:58.748 --> 00:53:02.228
better outcome by PFS and a strong biomarker

902
00:53:02.608 --> 00:53:05.608
score by receiver operator characteristic curve.

903
00:53:06.268 --> 00:53:08.978
The other thing it did is it was really interesting that we had pre- and

904
00:53:09.048 --> 00:53:12.688
post-treatment samples. And you can see in every one of them, the post-treatment

905
00:53:12.728 --> 00:53:15.508
sample was more resistant. Even those which we would have called sensitive were

906
00:53:15.568 --> 00:53:17.468
seven times more resistant than these.

907
00:53:17.488 --> 00:53:19.868
But the one I'm going to really point to is the worst one here,

908
00:53:20.828 --> 00:53:24.228
MM91, which had a huge change pre- and post.

909
00:53:24.528 --> 00:53:28.287
And so this was a patient of a colleague, Nizar Bahloul.

910
00:53:28.348 --> 00:53:29.638
And what Nizar found was

911
00:53:30.468 --> 00:53:34.388
he did single-cell CNV on this, thinking that maybe MCL1 was going to

912
00:53:34.428 --> 00:53:38.208
be changed and altered, and we did not see any changes in MCL1.

913
00:53:38.248 --> 00:53:41.768
And in fact, we treated that patient sample with the MCL1 inhibitor, and

914
00:53:41.808 --> 00:53:44.688
it was the most resistant we'd ever seen.

915
00:53:45.228 --> 00:53:49.048
What this patient had acquired was another of these BCL2 mutations,

916
00:53:49.128 --> 00:53:52.728
similar to what Andreas had mentioned early in his talk, and this was one that

917
00:53:52.808 --> 00:53:56.428
hadn't been characterized. We showed that, in fact, if you put this into

918
00:53:56.468 --> 00:54:00.308
cells, just like the G101V in the original CLL

919
00:54:00.348 --> 00:54:03.908
studies, it decreased the priming, particularly

920
00:54:04.528 --> 00:54:07.588
from the bad peptides shown in BCL2.

921
00:54:07.608 --> 00:54:10.268
The cells become very resistant, and very much like the

922
00:54:10.308 --> 00:54:14.248
G101V, it's still a functional BCL2.

923
00:54:14.328 --> 00:54:17.388
It binds Bim, but now the drug can no longer

924
00:54:18.048 --> 00:54:19.148
release the Bim from

925
00:54:20.428 --> 00:54:24.408
BCL2. Finally, I just want to show another example that

926
00:54:24.428 --> 00:54:28.148
we just recently published, where we worked with several groups at the Mayo Clinic,

927
00:54:29.408 --> 00:54:33.368
in Ostrava, and Memorial Sloan Kettering, and took all of our patients together

928
00:54:33.428 --> 00:54:34.728
who had been treated with venetoclax.

929
00:54:35.108 --> 00:54:38.928
And what we determined was patients who had RAS-activating mutations

930
00:54:39.148 --> 00:54:43.024
did worse. They had worse-Responses and did worse

931
00:54:43.164 --> 00:54:46.004
overall, very similar to what happens with the 1q gain.

932
00:54:46.404 --> 00:54:50.024
1q is where Mcl1 is, so that's another thing that can drive some of this

933
00:54:50.044 --> 00:54:53.604
resistance. And so we modeled this

934
00:54:54.104 --> 00:54:57.454
in cell lines by overexpressing either wild type or the

935
00:54:59.304 --> 00:55:03.104
activated Ras, and you only get an advantage with the activated Ras.

936
00:55:03.434 --> 00:55:07.384
And the activated Ras also is the only thing that also causes a change

937
00:55:07.464 --> 00:55:10.744
and lowers the overall priming on BCL2.

938
00:55:11.324 --> 00:55:14.024
So with that, I just want to conclude by saying that mitochondrial priming can be

939
00:55:14.063 --> 00:55:17.814
enhanced by therapy, providing the basis for the effective combination

940
00:55:17.844 --> 00:55:20.014
approaches when targeting apoptosis.

941
00:55:20.464 --> 00:55:24.224
The priming is inhibited by extrinsic factors such as stroma or cytokine

942
00:55:24.284 --> 00:55:27.874
factors, and this mechanism seems to be both transcriptional and

943
00:55:27.924 --> 00:55:31.024
post-translational regulation of BCL2 proteins, including

944
00:55:31.604 --> 00:55:34.584
regulation of Bim, which can also occur in an intrinsic fashion because we see it

945
00:55:34.624 --> 00:55:36.824
very constitutively in these cells.

946
00:55:36.864 --> 00:55:40.764
The 11;14 translocation, I should say there, sorry

947
00:55:40.824 --> 00:55:44.484
about that, is associated with BCL2 dependence and venetoclax sensitivity, and it

948
00:55:44.604 --> 00:55:46.464
seems to be related to an altered differentiation.

949
00:55:46.914 --> 00:55:50.384
And then finally, both extrinsic and intrinsic factors can actually

950
00:55:50.444 --> 00:55:52.124
overcome this type of resistance.

951
00:55:52.364 --> 00:55:54.704
So with that, I'd like to thank you, and happy to take any questions.

952
00:56:04.204 --> 00:56:07.764
I'll start with a question. I'm curious, have you looked at what

953
00:56:08.164 --> 00:56:12.004
changes are being caused by the Ras activation that then feed

954
00:56:12.064 --> 00:56:13.704
into this venetoclax resistance?

955
00:56:13.864 --> 00:56:15.264
Yeah. So that's what we're looking at.

956
00:56:15.284 --> 00:56:19.024
And so from AML, there's been studies that

957
00:56:19.064 --> 00:56:21.284
suggest it's actually inducing Mcl1.

958
00:56:21.464 --> 00:56:21.604
Mm-hmm.

959
00:56:22.024 --> 00:56:25.804
We don't see that, and in fact, in those cells that I showed at the end, where we

960
00:56:25.814 --> 00:56:29.704
had put the different Ras, the wild type or the activated

961
00:56:29.824 --> 00:56:30.054
in,

962
00:56:30.964 --> 00:56:32.724
we clearly see resistance to venetoclax.

963
00:56:33.324 --> 00:56:35.284
We see almost no change to the Mcl1 inhibitor.

964
00:56:35.324 --> 00:56:38.164
If anything, maybe a slight resistance to that.

965
00:56:38.194 --> 00:56:39.804
And we didn't see anything in the priming.

966
00:56:39.864 --> 00:56:42.144
So we don't think it's the change in Mcl1.

967
00:56:42.164 --> 00:56:45.104
And that kind of leads us back to other potential

968
00:56:45.864 --> 00:56:47.464
post-translational modification events.

969
00:56:47.524 --> 00:56:50.614
And one of the ones we're actually thinking about a lot right now is BAD, because

970
00:56:50.624 --> 00:56:52.924
it can be phosphorylated in that pathway as well.

971
00:56:53.384 --> 00:56:55.184
Yeah. It gets complicated.

972
00:56:56.124 --> 00:56:59.264
Hi. Great talk. I just have two question.

973
00:56:59.804 --> 00:57:03.004
So first is, I saw you combine with the

974
00:57:03.064 --> 00:57:06.724
BCL-xL with the BCL2, but

975
00:57:06.734 --> 00:57:10.464
does Mcl will complementary? Have you tested

