00:57:43.384 --> 00:57:46.644
The PROTAC actually is a pretty good one, and we've not gone back to revisit it.

989
00:57:46.684 --> 00:57:50.264
But I'd also be a little concerned about some of the potential toxicities.

990
00:57:50.444 --> 00:57:53.724
And David can comment on this. I don't think he thinks

991
00:57:54.184 --> 00:57:58.124
ABT-737 really inhibits BCL-xL at all, or very little, if I remember right.

992
00:57:58.264 --> 00:58:02.064
Yeah. Currently, I designed the siRNA, just combined

993
00:58:02.104 --> 00:58:06.024
both this one. We are exciting to find the 80%

994
00:58:06.084 --> 00:58:08.904
of the AML cell just die,

995
00:58:09.444 --> 00:58:13.184
apoptosis. So very interesting that we just combined those two

996
00:58:13.324 --> 00:58:15.624
siRNA to test it.

997
00:58:16.124 --> 00:58:19.904
Yeah, they clearly work, and in fact, actually, BCL2 and Mcl1

998
00:58:19.924 --> 00:58:21.603
inhibitors were tested clinically

999
00:58:22.444 --> 00:58:26.124
in AML, and they ended up having to stop it because of

1000
00:58:26.164 --> 00:58:27.104
toxicity.

1001
00:58:27.164 --> 00:58:28.764
And also, they have heart

1002
00:58:30.744 --> 00:58:34.584
