00:58:57.064 --> 00:59:00.544
people, I'm sure, are actively working on.

1011
00:59:00.644 --> 00:59:00.944
Thank you.

1012
00:59:02.664 --> 00:59:05.804
I was intrigued by your dexamethasone data.

1013
00:59:06.564 --> 00:59:07.324
How does that work?

1014
00:59:09.844 --> 00:59:10.444
So

1015
00:59:11.844 --> 00:59:14.934
I never actually understood why dexamethasone worked at anywhere, and I asked the

1016
00:59:15.104 --> 00:59:18.044
guy who ran our phase one clinic this one time, and I said, "Why do we put

1017
00:59:18.064 --> 00:59:20.704
dexamethasone in everything?" And he said, "Because dexamethasone is like bacon.

1018
00:59:20.744 --> 00:59:24.284
It goes well with everything." And I think the reason why he was right is it

1019
00:59:24.324 --> 00:59:25.024
induces Bim,

1020
00:59:25.824 --> 00:59:28.304
and because it induces Bim, it just increases your priming.

1021
00:59:28.364 --> 00:59:32.124
And it did it really across the board, but by having more

1022
00:59:32.564 --> 00:59:36.344
BCL2 priming alone, that seemed to be sufficient to

1023
00:59:36.644 --> 00:59:38.724
have enough release that you could actually kill the cell.

1024
00:59:38.764 --> 00:59:41.084
But is it known how it increases Bim?

1025
00:59:41.304 --> 00:59:42.084
It's transcriptional.

1026
00:59:43.454 --> 00:59:45.094
But through which pathway?

1027
00:59:46.804 --> 00:59:47.504
Which?

1028
00:59:47.524 --> 00:59:50.954
Which pathway is activated? Or is it dexamethasone directly?

1029
00:59:50.954 --> 00:59:51.804
It's the glucocorticoid receptor.

1030
00:59:51.844 --> 00:59:52.784
Is it directly?

1031
00:59:53.004 --> 00:59:53.124
Yeah.

1032
00:59:53.244 --> 00:59:53.484
Okay.

1033
00:59:55.144 --> 00:59:55.444
Thank you.

1034
00:59:55.684 --> 00:59:55.984
Sure.

1035
00:59:57.944 --> 00:59:59.783
Very nice talk. Congratulations.

1036
00:59:59.884 --> 01:00:03.844
I would like to make a comment on Mcl1 and cardiotox, because it

